Package: nco
Version: 2.8.4
Revision: 1
Description: The netCDF Operators
License: GPL
Maintainer: Takeshi Enomoto <takeshi@mac.com>

# Prerequisites
Depends: netcdf-shlibs (>=3.5.1-14), udunits (>=1.11.7-4)

# Unpack Phase:
Source: http://%n.sourceforge.net/%n.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 012a5d3a40e4c28ac51798d75fbbd418
SourceDirectory: %n-%v

# Compile Phase:
ConfigureParams: --prefix=%p --enable-shared=false --enable-dods=false --enable-optimize=true
CompileScript: <<
#	setenv NETCDF_INC %p/include
#	setenv NETCDF_LIB %p/lib
	./configure %c
	make
<<

# Install Phase:
DocFiles: <<
doc/ANNOUNCE doc/ChangeLog doc/LICENSE doc/NEWS
doc/README doc/TODO doc/help.txt doc/i18n.txt
doc/index.shtml doc/insure.txt doc/man_end.txt
doc/ncap.txt doc/nco.dvi doc/nco.html 
doc/nco.pdf doc/nco.ps doc/nco.txt
doc/nco.xml doc/nco_news.shtml doc/nco_src_frg.txt
doc/rtfm.txt
<<

InstallScript: <<
	make prefix=%i install mandir=%i/share/man infodir=%i/share/info
<<

DescDetail: <<
	Each NCO operator (e.g., ncks) takes netCDF or HDF input file(s),
	performs an operation (e.g., averaging, hyperslabbing, or renaming),
	and outputs a processed netCDF file. Although most users of
	netCDF and HDF data are involved in scientific research,
	these data formats, and thus NCO, are generic and
	are equally useful in fields like finance.
<<

Homepage: http://nco.sourceforge.net/

